						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar near the southern entrance into the Sōmēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1392 (?).</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Prajōtpatti (Prajāpati), Phālguṇa, ba. 5, Thursday.</hi> On palaeographical grounds, the record, may be assigned to the <hi rend="bold">14th Century A.D.</hi> The intended date might be <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1392 March 14.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records that Bhairavadēva, son of Kheyidēva, who was a servant of Kumāra Sivarāma Ayya, renovated the southern gate <hi rend="italic">(teṁkaṇa dāraṭa),</hi> obviously of the Sōmēśvara temple.</p>						

						</summary>
